cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper discusses measures for evaluating and improving the robustness of networks. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on network robustness. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses graph measures and their functionality as a measure for topological network robustness. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the ability of networks to continue to perform well when subject to failures or attacks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as some of the measures discussed in the paper are based on spectral graph theory.
